      <p>
        <s>The given scene is from the movie <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="title">The Hate U Give</ref> which was published in <date>2018</date> and directed by <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="director">George Tillmann Jr.</ref>.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>In the scene <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Starr</ref> and <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Chris</ref> are talking again after he tried to have sex with her.</s>
      </p>
      <p>
        <s>In the beginning of the scene <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Chris</ref> walks in the school.</s>
        <s><ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Starr</ref> sees him for the first time after he tried to have sex with her.</s>
        <s>She wasn't ready but he still tried it.</s>
        <s>This is why <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Starr</ref> is angry.</s>
        <s>She wants to cover her feelings for <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Chris</ref> by <choice><orig>beeing</orig><reg>being</reg></choice> cold to him.</s>
        <s><ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Chris</ref> wants to make <ref target="b10gk5_1" type="character">Starr</ref> happy.</s>
        <s>He wants to have a real relationship with her.</s>
      </p>
